---
By: Yoga Vasistha
Locus:
  Page: 354
  Verse: 14
Tags:
  - Peace
---
To the peaceful a house is like a forest and to the restless even a forest
is like a crowded city. To one who is at peace, the entire world is a
peaceful forest. To one who is restless with a thousand thoughts, it is an
ocean of sorrow.
